WEBVTT

00:00:00.440 --> 00:00:01.910
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

00:00:01.910 --> 00:00:03.610
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

00:00:03.610 --> 00:00:05.140
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

00:00:06.910 --> 00:00:08.280
The deal is off.

00:00:08.810 --> 00:00:09.810
What...

00:00:12.250 --> 00:00:13.250
Goodness.

00:00:17.460 --> 00:00:19.860
There will be no deal whatsoever
with Adele Group.

00:00:36.980 --> 00:00:38.480
(Episode 8)

00:00:41.210 --> 00:00:44.150
At first, I thought this was
just an aggressive takeover.

00:00:45.480 --> 00:00:47.250
You started in jewelry,

00:00:47.250 --> 00:00:50.020
then bought fashion,
cosmetic, and food firms.

00:00:50.860 --> 00:00:53.160
I figured you'd be targeting
the bio industry next.

00:00:56.630 --> 00:00:59.230
But planning a takeover
behind the CEO's back?

00:01:05.570 --> 00:01:06.570
And you.

00:01:08.740 --> 00:01:11.440
You actually agreed
to these illegal terms?

00:01:12.380 --> 00:01:14.780
CEO Baek, wait.

00:01:14.780 --> 00:01:15.810
You...

00:01:16.610 --> 00:01:19.380
moved your family to the US
and begged me for a job.

00:01:19.850 --> 00:01:21.650
You promised you'd give your all
to my company.

00:01:22.050 --> 00:01:23.420
That was over a decade ago.

00:01:24.360 --> 00:01:26.660
Does all our time working together
mean nothing to you?

00:01:28.190 --> 00:01:29.290
Fine.

00:01:29.430 --> 00:01:32.000
I've given you over a decade.
What do I have to show for it?

00:01:32.200 --> 00:01:35.170
The company is this successful.
I deserve my cut.

00:01:35.870 --> 00:01:37.840
I'm sick of walking on eggshells
around you.

00:01:38.370 --> 00:01:40.640
- I'm done being just an employee.
- Fine.

00:01:41.640 --> 00:01:43.340
Then quit, just like you want.

00:01:44.880 --> 00:01:46.140
The moment I return to the US,

00:01:46.710 --> 00:01:48.550
I'm firing you
as head of the Korean branch.

00:01:49.510 --> 00:01:52.650
I've also secured evidence
that you tried to sell the company.

00:01:52.880 --> 00:01:55.590
What? Evidence?

00:02:02.990 --> 00:02:04.930
You use backroom deals...

00:02:05.330 --> 00:02:06.700
to snatch other people's companies,

00:02:07.630 --> 00:02:10.500
and you embezzle funds
by inflating transaction prices.

00:02:12.470 --> 00:02:14.040
Rather than running a business,

00:02:14.340 --> 00:02:16.210
you've been building
a personal slush fund.

00:02:19.180 --> 00:02:21.350
Don't even think about coming
after my company again.

00:02:22.250 --> 00:02:24.180
I have the power to expose
Adele Group's illegal activities,

00:02:24.320 --> 00:02:26.480
and I am more than capable
of fighting back.

00:02:31.590 --> 00:02:35.260
CEO Baek, wait!

00:03:00.490 --> 00:03:02.290
I appreciate what you did
for me last time.

00:03:03.890 --> 00:03:06.090
And as for this...

00:03:07.190 --> 00:03:09.130
I feel I must return it.

00:03:10.930 --> 00:03:13.670
(Ihwachae)

00:03:15.300 --> 00:03:16.670
I appreciate the invitation,

00:03:17.100 --> 00:03:19.340
but I have no intention
of marrying my son off just yet.

00:03:19.540 --> 00:03:21.970
Your son is still quite young,
I know.

00:03:23.210 --> 00:03:24.780
But in a succession race,

00:03:25.210 --> 00:03:28.410
arranging his marriage early
will help.

00:03:29.710 --> 00:03:33.920
My son is helping me enough
just by maintaining his position.

00:03:34.690 --> 00:03:37.720
I intend to handle everything else
on my own.

00:03:41.790 --> 00:03:45.200
You really are one of a kind,
Director Kim.

00:03:46.400 --> 00:03:47.400
Pardon me?

00:03:47.630 --> 00:03:50.870
I've seen plenty of parents...

00:03:51.440 --> 00:03:54.940
use their kids' marriages
for their own ambitions.

00:03:55.810 --> 00:03:58.310
So when I meet...

00:03:58.310 --> 00:04:00.780
someone like you
who thinks differently,

00:04:00.910 --> 00:04:03.650
I feel compelled to help
however I can.

00:04:05.520 --> 00:04:06.780
Even if it's not about marriage,

00:04:07.620 --> 00:04:10.150
if you ever need help,
don't hesitate to come to me.

00:04:11.460 --> 00:04:12.820
Please, indulge an old woman.

00:04:12.990 --> 00:04:14.460
(Ihwachae)

00:04:15.790 --> 00:04:17.660
I'd be very pleased
if you'd accept it.

00:04:22.530 --> 00:04:23.530
Thank you.

00:04:24.870 --> 00:04:26.440
(Ihwachae)

00:04:27.440 --> 00:04:29.540
Your son is a lucky man.

00:04:30.340 --> 00:04:34.150
While others scramble
to arrange marriages for succession,

00:04:34.650 --> 00:04:36.150
he gets to study abroad in the UK,

00:04:36.410 --> 00:04:40.350
and with his girlfriend, no less.

00:04:43.520 --> 00:04:46.460
I seem to know quite a lot, don't I?

00:04:49.290 --> 00:04:50.300
That's right.

00:04:51.400 --> 00:04:53.330
This is what Ihwachae is like.

00:04:55.100 --> 00:04:57.900
Through the relationships
we've built over decades,

00:04:59.270 --> 00:05:01.270
we hear many things.

00:05:04.580 --> 00:05:05.640
I see.

00:05:09.080 --> 00:05:12.780
Min Jun is studying abroad?
With his girlfriend?

00:05:26.130 --> 00:05:27.870
Goodness. Mother?

00:05:39.280 --> 00:05:40.410
Hello.

00:05:43.380 --> 00:05:44.380
Nice to meet you.

00:05:45.750 --> 00:05:47.150
What brings you to campus?

00:05:48.290 --> 00:05:50.150
I came to talk to you
about something,

00:05:50.620 --> 00:05:52.320
but I see you were
with your girlfriend.

00:05:53.290 --> 00:05:55.060
No, it's not like that.
She's just...

00:05:58.900 --> 00:06:00.800
How did you know I had a girlfriend?

00:06:02.100 --> 00:06:03.330
Mother, did you...

00:06:03.670 --> 00:06:06.670
Since we're here, we might as well
discuss you studying abroad.

00:06:10.310 --> 00:06:12.380
You should go to the UK on your own.

00:06:12.780 --> 00:06:15.910
I'm sorry,
but Min Jun will not be going.

00:06:25.790 --> 00:06:28.060
Wait. Mother.

00:06:36.830 --> 00:06:39.340
I was just about to ask
which university he was going to.

00:06:42.440 --> 00:06:44.010
He's not studying abroad?

00:06:45.380 --> 00:06:47.350
So his family is against it?

00:06:48.450 --> 00:06:52.420
Then that means he can't go
with Baek Jin Ju.

00:06:59.290 --> 00:07:00.290
Studying abroad isn't an option.

00:07:04.560 --> 00:07:07.500
Too many things can
go wrong overseas. It's dangerous.

00:07:08.100 --> 00:07:11.340
Once the succession battle begins,
they might try to hurt you.

00:07:13.000 --> 00:07:15.840
Once Dr. Baek's evidence arrives
and they feel cornered,

00:07:15.940 --> 00:07:18.710
Oh Jung Ran might try to kill you.

00:07:24.180 --> 00:07:25.680
You need to stay by my side.

00:07:26.320 --> 00:07:27.850
It's the only way I can protect you.

00:07:33.660 --> 00:07:35.360
Nothing dangerous will happen...

00:07:37.730 --> 00:07:39.730
because I'm giving up
my claim to succession.

00:07:41.270 --> 00:07:42.270
What?

00:07:43.470 --> 00:07:46.970
Being the heir to Adele Group
is something I have never wanted.

00:07:51.040 --> 00:07:53.240
I wish you'd let all of this go...

00:07:55.380 --> 00:07:57.720
- and just live in peace.
- No.

00:07:58.720 --> 00:08:01.190
You are the heir,
the rightful owner of Adele Group.

00:08:02.120 --> 00:08:03.550
We're so close.

00:08:04.020 --> 00:08:07.290
Once we play our final card,
we'll win.

00:08:08.330 --> 00:08:09.530
For my sake,

00:08:10.660 --> 00:08:12.300
for your own mother,

00:08:12.830 --> 00:08:15.100
you must become
the head of Adele Group.

00:08:18.940 --> 00:08:21.310
I really thought you were different.

00:08:26.140 --> 00:08:28.050
But you're just like the rest
of them, aren't you?

00:08:29.550 --> 00:08:30.650
You don't want to protect me.

00:08:30.650 --> 00:08:32.420
You were just using me...

00:08:34.320 --> 00:08:35.790
to take over the company.

00:08:37.990 --> 00:08:38.990
I...

00:08:39.860 --> 00:08:41.190
used you?

00:08:44.530 --> 00:08:45.630
You can't do this.

00:08:46.130 --> 00:08:49.900
My 20 years of work and your future.
It's all on the line!

00:08:52.440 --> 00:08:54.040
You can't just run away...

00:08:54.040 --> 00:08:56.540
because of some silly crush
on a girl.

00:08:56.540 --> 00:08:58.940
I'm not running away.
I'm being brave!

00:09:02.880 --> 00:09:05.780
I'm brave enough
to choose my own future.

00:09:15.090 --> 00:09:16.760
I'm a grown man.

00:09:18.660 --> 00:09:19.960
I don't need your permission.

00:09:26.400 --> 00:09:27.410
You're right.

00:09:28.140 --> 00:09:29.910
I did want to protect you,

00:09:30.740 --> 00:09:32.880
but maybe I was using you, too.

00:09:34.150 --> 00:09:35.150
But still...

00:09:36.380 --> 00:09:37.420
I...

00:09:38.580 --> 00:09:39.620
Even so,

00:09:42.290 --> 00:09:43.920
don't do anything reckless.

00:09:45.020 --> 00:09:47.460
This will get complicated
if your father finds out.

00:09:59.500 --> 00:10:00.570
Are you okay?

00:10:01.240 --> 00:10:03.610
You look so pale.
Maybe you should see a doctor.

00:10:04.340 --> 00:10:05.340
I'm fine.

00:10:09.080 --> 00:10:10.080
Where's Min Jun?

00:10:10.820 --> 00:10:12.180
He went up to his room.

00:10:13.620 --> 00:10:14.920
I'm going...

00:10:15.350 --> 00:10:17.820
to put someone on Min Jun
for a while.

00:10:18.520 --> 00:10:19.520
Put someone on him?

00:10:20.220 --> 00:10:22.360
You don't mean spy on him, do you?

00:10:22.630 --> 00:10:24.160
Call it a security detail,
if you want.

00:10:24.800 --> 00:10:26.660
That's what you can tell Min Jun.

00:10:27.160 --> 00:10:30.100
Call it a security detail,
but he'll think he's being spied on.

00:10:31.100 --> 00:10:33.800
That should keep him
from doing anything reckless.

00:10:34.640 --> 00:10:37.110
I must stop him from going abroad,
even if it means doing this.

00:10:38.140 --> 00:10:40.680
At least until the evidence
from Dr. Baek arrives.

00:10:41.310 --> 00:10:42.510
Just until then.

00:10:42.980 --> 00:10:46.480
- But...
- I can't sit by and do nothing.

00:10:47.890 --> 00:10:50.790
I need to put a lid on this
before Chairman Park finds out.

00:10:51.890 --> 00:10:52.890
Please.

00:10:54.760 --> 00:10:55.830
All right.

00:11:08.370 --> 00:11:09.640
I'm sorry.

00:11:09.970 --> 00:11:12.310
It's the director's orders,
so my hands are tied.

00:11:12.580 --> 00:11:13.980
The security is just an excuse.

00:11:13.980 --> 00:11:15.950
She's telling me to stay home.

00:11:17.050 --> 00:11:19.750
So she's tying my hands
and telling me to do nothing?

00:11:19.950 --> 00:11:21.150
She's just worried about you.

00:11:21.150 --> 00:11:23.720
I don't think it's me
she's worried about.

00:11:26.290 --> 00:11:28.430
You know how she feels
better than anyone.

00:11:28.960 --> 00:11:31.500
Things are just
very complicated right now,

00:11:32.030 --> 00:11:33.260
so please try to understand.

00:11:37.230 --> 00:11:40.940
Try not to be too upset.
I'll be on my way.

00:11:49.080 --> 00:11:50.080
You know,

00:11:50.650 --> 00:11:53.120
I've noticed something
for a while now.

00:11:54.090 --> 00:11:56.720
Both you and Secretary Jung...

00:11:56.720 --> 00:12:00.360
always clam up mid-sentence
when I show up.

00:12:01.530 --> 00:12:04.700
I'm a pretty easygoing guy,
but it's getting on my nerves.

00:12:05.760 --> 00:12:08.300
What's so secret
that you have to leave me out?

00:12:08.800 --> 00:12:09.800
Come on.

00:12:10.470 --> 00:12:13.200
What doesn't she want you
to be upset about?

00:12:16.870 --> 00:12:19.240
So it's the silent treatment now?
All right, fine.

00:12:19.240 --> 00:12:20.340
I'm used to it.

00:12:20.740 --> 00:12:23.510
Come on, what is it?
What's so serious?

00:12:34.130 --> 00:12:35.560
Just give up.

00:12:40.230 --> 00:12:43.330
It's your mom, not mine,
who's going this far.

00:12:43.330 --> 00:12:45.740
You can kiss
studying abroad goodbye.

00:12:49.110 --> 00:12:51.610
To be honest,
I was really rooting for you.

00:12:52.080 --> 00:12:54.180
I really wanted you
to be able to go.

00:12:55.580 --> 00:12:56.580
Of course.

00:12:56.810 --> 00:12:59.420
With me out of the way,
you can become the heir to Adele.

00:13:00.280 --> 00:13:01.290
Hey.

00:13:03.550 --> 00:13:06.290
Why do you always have to lump me in
with my mom?

00:13:07.160 --> 00:13:09.060
I have my own path,

00:13:09.060 --> 00:13:11.030
just like
how you dreamed of studying abroad.

00:13:11.030 --> 00:13:12.030
It's just that, unlike you,

00:13:13.260 --> 00:13:14.900
I haven't been able to act on it.

00:13:17.070 --> 00:13:20.200
You're not the only one who suffered
being caught between our two moms.

00:13:20.300 --> 00:13:22.670
Being the successor of Adele
isn't my thing either.

00:13:22.670 --> 00:13:24.780
I just haven't figured out
what I really want to do yet.

00:13:24.840 --> 00:13:26.110
That's why I've been lying low.

00:13:26.110 --> 00:13:28.910
But once I find my passion,
I'll be unstoppable, you know.

00:13:30.710 --> 00:13:32.480
So you had a plan all along.

00:13:32.480 --> 00:13:33.820
Of course I did!

00:13:37.250 --> 00:13:39.690
What did you take me for
all this time?

00:13:40.930 --> 00:13:43.830
You always seemed so carefree,
like everything was easy for you.

00:13:43.890 --> 00:13:45.930
You thought I was taking it easy
without a care in the world?

00:13:47.160 --> 00:13:48.670
I must have seemed pathetic to you.

00:13:49.100 --> 00:13:50.200
In a way,

00:13:51.270 --> 00:13:52.270
I was a little jealous.

00:13:56.410 --> 00:13:57.440
At least,

00:13:57.810 --> 00:13:59.380
you looked like
you were enjoying life.

00:14:05.080 --> 00:14:08.790
Wait. Is that why
you've been avoiding me?

00:14:09.890 --> 00:14:10.920
Because you were jealous?

00:14:11.690 --> 00:14:13.890
No, because you were so obnoxious.

00:14:14.760 --> 00:14:16.430
You little punk.

00:14:18.400 --> 00:14:20.560
What's with this vibe?

00:14:20.900 --> 00:14:23.100
It's like we're actual brothers
who get along.

00:14:23.130 --> 00:14:26.800
Don't get excited.
We've just gotten a little closer.

00:14:27.640 --> 00:14:30.570
Fine. I guess we're friends
who are like brothers,

00:14:30.570 --> 00:14:32.540
or brothers who are like friends.

00:14:33.740 --> 00:14:35.550
Since your plans
to go abroad are ruined,

00:14:35.750 --> 00:14:37.350
your big brother
will go easy on you.

00:14:38.580 --> 00:14:41.190
Who says I can't go?
I'm going to keep pushing forward.

00:14:42.050 --> 00:14:43.720
What are you going to do
about your mom?

00:14:46.220 --> 00:14:47.590
Speaking of which...

00:14:50.490 --> 00:14:52.060
I need you to meet Jin Ju for me.

00:14:53.060 --> 00:14:55.330
Me? You want me to meet Baek Jin Ju?

00:14:55.400 --> 00:14:58.100
Just finish preparing with her.

00:14:58.100 --> 00:14:59.340
Once everything is ready,

00:15:00.300 --> 00:15:01.670
I'll leave, one way or another.

00:15:04.440 --> 00:15:05.640
I'm counting on you.

00:15:06.640 --> 00:15:10.510
Hey, we just started getting along,
so a huge favor like this...

00:15:15.120 --> 00:15:18.490
How could I possibly say no?
I can't.

00:15:23.230 --> 00:15:24.230
Okay.

00:15:25.200 --> 00:15:28.270
Let's get you out of here first.
In return,

00:15:28.730 --> 00:15:31.540
when it's my turn to escape,
you have to promise me you'll...

00:15:31.540 --> 00:15:32.640
I'll help you.

00:15:35.740 --> 00:15:36.740
Deal.

00:15:38.010 --> 00:15:39.010
Deal.

00:15:42.480 --> 00:15:44.620
Park Hyun Jun!

00:15:46.920 --> 00:15:49.520
Where on earth
did he run off to now?

00:15:49.520 --> 00:15:52.160
Who does he think
I'm worrying myself sick over?

00:15:53.520 --> 00:15:54.960
I can't take this anymore.

00:15:58.830 --> 00:16:01.800
Why can Kim Myung Hui be invited
but not me?

00:16:02.830 --> 00:16:06.100
What if that Kim Myung Hui manages
to marry her son into a good family?

00:16:07.140 --> 00:16:08.310
That can't happen.

00:16:08.570 --> 00:16:10.610
I must stop her, no matter the cost.

00:16:15.280 --> 00:16:17.820
I thought I warned you clearly.

00:16:18.480 --> 00:16:20.920
I told you to stay out of it
since marriage and succession...

00:16:20.920 --> 00:16:22.220
are my call.

00:16:23.550 --> 00:16:24.560
Wait a second.

00:16:25.020 --> 00:16:26.460
That tramp Kim Myung Hui...

00:16:26.460 --> 00:16:28.690
took matters into her own hands
and went to Ihwachae.

00:16:29.990 --> 00:16:31.030
That's right.

00:16:31.300 --> 00:16:33.400
An eye for an eye,
a tooth for a tooth.

00:16:33.760 --> 00:16:35.930
I'll give her a taste
of her own medicine.

00:16:50.480 --> 00:16:52.280
But you're just like the rest
of them, aren't you?

00:16:52.680 --> 00:16:53.980
You don't want to protect me.

00:16:53.980 --> 00:16:55.720
You were just using me...

00:16:57.420 --> 00:16:58.960
to take over the company.

00:17:09.900 --> 00:17:12.340
The New Design Competition prelims
are out.

00:17:12.840 --> 00:17:14.200
Three winners were selected...

00:17:14.200 --> 00:17:16.340
from the jewelry, fashion,
and cosmetics categories.

00:17:16.710 --> 00:17:19.280
We'll proceed to the finals
after receiving additional designs.

00:17:19.940 --> 00:17:22.950
Here are the winners
from our jewelry division.

00:17:23.010 --> 00:17:26.850
(Jewelry Division,
Director Kim Myung Hui)

00:17:29.290 --> 00:17:31.020
Try not to worry too much.

00:17:32.090 --> 00:17:34.630
The evidence from Dr. Baek
will be here soon.

00:17:34.990 --> 00:17:36.560
Once the whole truth comes out,

00:17:37.090 --> 00:17:39.130
I'm sure Min Jun will understand.

00:17:40.560 --> 00:17:42.800
Do I even deserve his understanding?

00:17:44.130 --> 00:17:46.400
I used Min Jun for my revenge.

00:17:46.600 --> 00:17:47.910
Used him?

00:17:48.640 --> 00:17:50.970
You did your best for Min Jun.

00:17:50.970 --> 00:17:51.980
No.

00:17:52.680 --> 00:17:55.880
I did all this for revenge,
not for Min Jun.

00:17:57.350 --> 00:17:59.820
I kept telling myself that
Min Jun would take over Adele.

00:18:00.820 --> 00:18:03.190
That it was
the only possible outcome.

00:18:05.760 --> 00:18:07.890
I never even considered
the kind of future...

00:18:08.460 --> 00:18:09.730
Min Jun wanted for himself.

00:18:10.630 --> 00:18:12.560
But that's just...

00:18:12.560 --> 00:18:13.900
Just look at me now.

00:18:14.500 --> 00:18:16.130
Min Jun wants
to find his own happiness...

00:18:16.400 --> 00:18:17.870
and his own future,

00:18:18.970 --> 00:18:19.970
and yet...

00:18:21.310 --> 00:18:23.140
I have no intention of giving in.

00:18:23.140 --> 00:18:24.580
I can't let him go.

00:18:26.480 --> 00:18:28.650
Because even at a time like this,
I have to seek justice.

00:18:34.380 --> 00:18:36.350
You lost your sister so unfairly.

00:18:37.020 --> 00:18:40.020
You've fought tooth and nail
for over 20 years to get justice for her.

00:18:40.090 --> 00:18:42.090
How can you
give it all up overnight?

00:18:43.490 --> 00:18:45.630
Even if Dr. Baek's evidence arrives,

00:18:46.260 --> 00:18:47.600
you can't send Jung Ran to prison...

00:18:47.600 --> 00:18:49.300
because the statute of limitations
has expired.

00:18:50.930 --> 00:18:53.240
The only way to make
Oh Jung Ran pay...

00:18:54.040 --> 00:18:57.010
is to take away Adele Group,
the thing she wants most.

00:18:57.940 --> 00:18:58.980
What else can you do?

00:18:59.910 --> 00:19:02.780
You can't give up
because there's no other option.

00:19:08.320 --> 00:19:10.750
So even if you feel bad
about what it's doing to Min Jun,

00:19:14.590 --> 00:19:15.890
don't be so hard on yourself.

00:19:46.920 --> 00:19:49.660
Are you really Min Jun's friend?

00:19:51.230 --> 00:19:52.900
Well, you see...

00:19:53.430 --> 00:19:55.830
We're like brothers who are friends,
or friends who are like brothers.

00:20:00.440 --> 00:20:01.770
Then that means you know.

00:20:02.870 --> 00:20:03.870
Know what?

00:20:04.240 --> 00:20:06.580
What happened to Min Jun?

00:20:06.580 --> 00:20:08.510
He says it's nothing serious,

00:20:08.580 --> 00:20:10.350
but something feels off.

00:20:10.810 --> 00:20:13.680
Something's up at home, right?

00:20:20.890 --> 00:20:22.830
Look, you should just call him.

00:20:22.890 --> 00:20:25.030
Going there will only make it worse.

00:20:25.100 --> 00:20:26.200
I'm still going.

00:20:26.200 --> 00:20:27.460
I want to be with him.

00:20:27.660 --> 00:20:28.700
Hey!

00:20:30.330 --> 00:20:34.140
I've always known
he avoids talking about his family.

00:20:34.810 --> 00:20:38.410
I had a feeling
home wasn't a happy place for him.

00:20:38.880 --> 00:20:42.110
And now you're telling me
he's stuck there all by himself?

00:20:43.250 --> 00:20:45.850
I don't know what's going on,
but I want to be there for him.

00:20:45.980 --> 00:20:48.920
Even if I can't see him in person,
I'll wait outside the gate.

00:20:50.990 --> 00:20:53.290
You're serious about him.

00:20:57.190 --> 00:20:58.200
Fine.

00:20:58.860 --> 00:21:00.660
If this is the Baek Jin Ju effect...

00:21:05.700 --> 00:21:07.170
Then I can rise to the challenge.

00:21:08.370 --> 00:21:09.640
I'll be the one...

00:21:09.970 --> 00:21:12.340
to get you through my family's gates
before Min Jun does.

00:21:20.680 --> 00:21:23.020
- Hello?
- Is this Choi Yu Na?

00:21:23.520 --> 00:21:25.020
Yes, speaking.

00:21:25.220 --> 00:21:27.460
Hi, this is the Adele Group calling.

00:21:27.460 --> 00:21:29.890
You entered
our New Design Competition.

00:21:29.960 --> 00:21:33.360
- I did.
- You've passed the first round.

00:21:33.630 --> 00:21:37.000
You must submit additional designs
for the final evaluation.

00:21:37.500 --> 00:21:38.840
Additional designs?

00:21:55.090 --> 00:21:57.020
But I already submitted
all my best work.

00:21:57.820 --> 00:22:00.560
How can I come up with more designs
all of a sudden?

00:23:06.890 --> 00:23:09.130
- What the...
- You!

00:23:10.090 --> 00:23:11.700
Hey, you.

00:23:12.400 --> 00:23:13.500
Get over here.

00:23:15.300 --> 00:23:16.300
What?

00:23:18.970 --> 00:23:20.270
We're at the office.

00:23:21.140 --> 00:23:22.410
Isn't she...

00:23:23.710 --> 00:23:25.240
Park Min Jun's mom?

00:23:25.440 --> 00:23:27.480
You brazen tramp.

00:23:27.810 --> 00:23:31.380
You sabotaged my plans
to find Hyun Jun a good wife,

00:23:31.820 --> 00:23:34.620
and then went to Ihwachae
to find a match for your son?

00:23:35.250 --> 00:23:38.890
Do you think the son of a mistress
can take over Adele that way?

00:23:39.720 --> 00:23:43.260
Adele belongs to my son,
and nothing is going to change that.

00:23:45.530 --> 00:23:48.500
Do you know
what my favorite saying is?

00:23:49.370 --> 00:23:51.900
An eye for an eye,
a tooth for a tooth.

00:23:52.500 --> 00:23:54.840
It means I'll pay you back in kind.

00:23:55.640 --> 00:23:56.940
Pay me back in kind,

00:23:57.640 --> 00:23:58.840
you say?

00:24:00.780 --> 00:24:02.410
Myung Hui.

00:24:02.780 --> 00:24:05.020
Myung Hui, don't go.

00:24:05.020 --> 00:24:07.220
Please, don't go!

00:24:07.420 --> 00:24:10.290
Myung Hui!

00:24:10.590 --> 00:24:14.090
How can I let her go? Myung Hui!

00:24:14.090 --> 00:24:15.360
Myung Hui...

00:24:19.900 --> 00:24:21.200
Just you wait.

00:24:22.070 --> 00:24:25.640
I'll ruin everything for you,
be it Ihwachae or anything else.

00:24:31.210 --> 00:24:32.280
Fine.

00:24:32.880 --> 00:24:37.810
I knew I could never forgive you
or let this go.

00:24:38.750 --> 00:24:41.650
If taking over Adele is the only way
to crush you,

00:24:42.520 --> 00:24:44.220
then I have no choice
but to see it through.

00:24:57.270 --> 00:24:58.370
So...

00:24:59.670 --> 00:25:00.870
Park Min Jun...

00:25:01.840 --> 00:25:03.640
is an heir to the Adele Group?

00:25:11.850 --> 00:25:15.050
(Adele Group New Design Competition)

00:25:41.650 --> 00:25:43.850
(Jewelry Division: Choi Yu Na)

00:25:43.910 --> 00:25:47.220
(Park Tae Ho)

00:25:47.320 --> 00:25:50.090
(Park Tae Ho)

00:25:50.150 --> 00:25:51.150
You ready?

00:26:10.070 --> 00:26:13.340
If I'm seen walking in with a girl,
it'll be a headache for everyone.

00:26:14.080 --> 00:26:15.610
Thanks for helping me.

00:26:18.210 --> 00:26:19.220
Well then.

00:26:23.590 --> 00:26:24.720
Just make sure we don't get caught.

00:26:36.800 --> 00:26:38.030
Be careful.

00:26:38.970 --> 00:26:39.970
Hyun Jun?

00:26:43.270 --> 00:26:44.770
Who's that with you?

00:26:45.480 --> 00:26:47.410
- Is that a friend of yours?
- Yes!

00:26:48.080 --> 00:26:49.280
A friend.

00:26:50.680 --> 00:26:52.650
You brought a friend home?

00:26:53.720 --> 00:26:55.190
You've never done that before.

00:26:55.190 --> 00:26:57.350
Right. Exactly.

00:26:57.750 --> 00:26:59.990
That's exactly why I wanted to do it
at least once.

00:26:59.990 --> 00:27:01.930
I figured I should try it once
before I graduate.

00:27:01.990 --> 00:27:03.630
Really?

00:27:06.200 --> 00:27:08.570
Why come here instead of the annex?

00:27:09.530 --> 00:27:12.400
Right, exactly.
Mr. Song, just a moment.

00:27:13.640 --> 00:27:16.510
It's the first time
I've ever brought a friend home,

00:27:16.570 --> 00:27:18.170
and it would be
pretty embarrassing...

00:27:18.170 --> 00:27:20.140
to take him to the annex.

00:27:20.580 --> 00:27:22.610
I can't exactly tell him
I was kicked out.

00:27:25.680 --> 00:27:26.680
That's a good point.

00:27:27.420 --> 00:27:29.620
So if you could help make sure
we're not interrupted...

00:27:29.620 --> 00:27:31.890
Right, of course. Head upstairs.

00:27:32.860 --> 00:27:34.620
- Thanks, Mr. Song.
- Sure.

00:27:40.000 --> 00:27:41.000
Go on upstairs.

00:27:47.440 --> 00:27:50.410
All right, let's go, buddy.

00:27:51.210 --> 00:27:52.580
How about we play a game?

00:27:56.680 --> 00:27:57.680
Want to play a game?

00:27:58.250 --> 00:28:00.920
He brought a friend home.

00:28:03.220 --> 00:28:04.220
What's going on?

00:28:05.260 --> 00:28:07.290
She said she had to see you,
no matter what.

00:28:08.590 --> 00:28:09.690
So I got a little creative.

00:28:24.240 --> 00:28:26.140
Park Min Jun is an Adele Group heir.

00:28:27.440 --> 00:28:30.350
If I can get him,
I could get Adele Group.

00:28:32.620 --> 00:28:34.380
But of all people,
Baek Jin Ju is with him...

00:28:35.420 --> 00:28:36.420
and could get Adele Group.

00:28:40.260 --> 00:28:42.290
Seriously? You scared me!

00:28:42.590 --> 00:28:44.330
Where's Jin Ju?

00:28:45.660 --> 00:28:48.260
Jin Ju this, Jin Ju that.
Enough already.

00:28:48.260 --> 00:28:49.500
You're the one who needs to stop.

00:28:50.070 --> 00:28:52.500
Call her and tell her
to come here now.

00:28:53.540 --> 00:28:54.540
Why should I?

00:28:55.610 --> 00:28:57.410
If it's that urgent,
you call her yourself.

00:28:58.040 --> 00:28:59.280
Why, you brat.

00:29:13.590 --> 00:29:16.460
From now on,
don't avoid me like you did today.

00:29:18.090 --> 00:29:20.730
If your mother finds out,
let's convince her together.

00:29:21.330 --> 00:29:24.700
If we work together,
we might be able to find a way.

00:29:26.770 --> 00:29:29.770
You're right.
If we do this together...

00:29:32.940 --> 00:29:35.750
With you by my side,
I feel like I can do anything.

00:29:43.320 --> 00:29:46.820
You want me to beg Baek Jin Ju?

00:29:47.790 --> 00:29:50.990
There's no other way
to convince CEO Baek.

00:29:51.290 --> 00:29:52.900
He dotes on her,

00:29:52.900 --> 00:29:55.000
so if Jin Ju asks,
he'll definitely give us a pass.

00:29:55.060 --> 00:29:57.200
- Dad.
- I know.

00:29:57.500 --> 00:29:59.140
I know it's humiliating.

00:29:59.300 --> 00:30:02.670
But if I get fired,
our family's finished.

00:30:03.070 --> 00:30:05.580
If you put up with this
and help me just this once...

00:30:05.580 --> 00:30:07.040
I'd rather die.

00:30:07.880 --> 00:30:08.880
Choi Yu Na!

00:30:09.610 --> 00:30:11.050
I know you don't want to do this,

00:30:11.050 --> 00:30:13.320
but how can you ask me
to kill you instead?

00:30:13.350 --> 00:30:14.480
Not me.

00:30:15.450 --> 00:30:17.090
I'm telling you to kill CEO Baek.

00:30:18.190 --> 00:30:19.990
What?

00:30:22.030 --> 00:30:24.560
You call him a friend,
but you're always kissing up to him.

00:30:26.160 --> 00:30:29.400
Because you're so pathetic,
I'm losing everything to Jin Ju.

00:30:30.300 --> 00:30:31.300
I...

00:30:33.040 --> 00:30:35.240
would rather die
than lose to her like this.

00:30:37.970 --> 00:30:39.610
So don't you dare lose either.

00:30:40.040 --> 00:30:42.680
If you can't take what you want,
kill to keep what you have.

00:30:43.050 --> 00:30:44.280
Don't you dare...

00:30:45.250 --> 00:30:47.580
drag me down with you
and make me suffer too!

00:31:11.840 --> 00:31:14.180
Rather than using Choi Sam Sik,

00:31:14.610 --> 00:31:16.380
we should use Choi Yu Na.

00:31:16.980 --> 00:31:18.680
Yes, sir.
I'll make the arrangements.

00:32:07.800 --> 00:32:10.770
(Pearl in Red)

00:32:11.130 --> 00:32:12.940
Myung Hui, that's enough.

00:32:13.140 --> 00:32:16.410
If you stir up trouble again,
you'll be in for a world of hurt.

00:32:16.970 --> 00:32:18.070
Adele isn't a good choice.

00:32:18.640 --> 00:32:20.740
It could be more dangerous
than you think.

00:32:20.980 --> 00:32:22.750
Why does Baek Jin Ju get everything?

00:32:22.750 --> 00:32:25.550
She gets both Min Jun and Adele.
How's that fair?

00:32:26.280 --> 00:32:27.950
What is it?
Weren't you done talking?

00:32:28.050 --> 00:32:31.390
I'm willing to do whatever you ask,
Chairman Park.

00:32:32.820 --> 00:32:34.820
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)